You can create a [BEFORE UPDATE trigger][1] that prevents the row from being updated if the current value of `Status` is `-1`:
 
    DELIMITER //
    
    CREATE TRIGGER trg_before_update
    BEFORE UPDATE
    ON tablename FOR EACH ROW
    BEGIN
      IF OLD.Status = -1 THEN
        SIGNAL SQLSTATE &#39;45000&#39; 
        SET MESSAGE_TEXT = &#39;The row can&#39;&#39;t be updated because the status is -1&#39;;
      END IF;
    END//
    
    DELIMITER ;

Change `tablename` to the name of your table.&lt;br/&gt;

